The scope of a variable refers to the part of the program in which the variable is accessible.
Here is an example that illustrates the difference between local and global variables:

public class Main {
  // global variable
  static int global = 123;

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    // local variable
    int local = 456;

    System.out.println(global); // 123
    System.out.println(local); // 456
  }
}
